      <div class="mb-14">
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mb-3">Pick a sandbox backend per environment</h3>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-fg-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-4 max-w-3xl">
          Environments — the reusable packages/networking/image config sessions
          attach to — now carry their own sandbox provider reference on
          self-hosted Node deployments, instead of everything sharing one global
          <code class="font-mono text-sm">SANDBOX_PROVIDER</code>. Set
          <code class="font-mono text-sm">config.sandbox_provider</code> to any
          registered provider ID (system or BYOK). The Console's
          environment-create picker queries
          <code class="font-mono text-sm">GET /v1/hosting_types</code> to show
          what's available — including any user-registered BYOK providers.
        </p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-start">
          <pre class="bg-[var(--color-bg)] border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-4 text-xs leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto"><code>GET /v1/hosting_types
&#123;
  "data": [
    &#123; "id": "cloud", "label": "Cloud" &#125;,
    &#123; "id": "subprocess", "label": "Local subprocess" &#125;,
    &#123; "id": "litebox", "label": "LiteBox (local micro-VM)" &#125;,
    &#123; "id": "boxrun", "label": "BoxRun (remote micro-VM)" &#125;,
    &#123; "id": "daytona", "label": "Daytona" &#125;,
    &#123; "id": "e2b", "label": "E2B" &#125;,
