      "description": "External sandbox provider (daytona) — BYOK", "external": true &#125;
  ]
&#125;

# Environment config referencing a BYOK provider
&#123;
  "config": &#123;
    "sandbox_provider": "my-daytona-prod",
    "packages": &#123; "pip": ["numpy", "pandas"] &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-fg-muted)] leading-relaxed text-sm">
            Mix isolation levels across environments on the same host — trusted
            internal tooling on cheap subprocess isolation, customer-facing
            work on a hardware-isolated micro-VM or Kubernetes pod — without a
            redeploy or a harness change. Add your own provider keys via
