        <div class="lg:col-span-7">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mb-3">Structured progress for multi-hour tasks</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-fg-muted)] leading-relaxed text-sm">
            A new <code class="font-mono text-sm">agent.status</code> event carries
            a structured heartbeat — <code class="font-mono text-xs">state</code>,
            <code class="font-mono text-xs">summary</code>, <code class="font-mono text-xs">step</code>,
            <code class="font-mono text-xs">total_steps</code>, <code class="font-mono text-xs">blocked_on</code>
            — instead of free-text progress buried in <code class="font-mono text-sm">agent.message</code>.
            The default harness emits one per model turn; the <code class="font-mono text-sm">long-running</code>
            harness additionally fires a wall-clock heartbeat (default every 60s)
            so a single very long tool call still reports life, and marks
            <code class="font-mono text-xs">state: "blocked"</code> when a turn
            ends waiting on tool confirmation. These events are excluded from
            model context entirely, so heartbeats can't perturb the byte-deterministic
            prompt-cache prefix or force early compaction — and the step counter
            reseeds from the durable event log on crash recovery, so numbering
            survives a restart without gaps or duplicates.
          </p>
        </div>
