            <code class="font-mono text-sm">slack_message</code>,
            <code class="font-mono text-sm">matrix_message</code> — each naming a
            vault credential and a destination. <code class="font-mono text-sm">packages/github</code>
            and <code class="font-mono text-sm">packages/slack</code> gained a
            <code class="font-mono text-sm">notify.ts</code>, and a new
            <code class="font-mono text-sm">packages/matrix</code> package ships
            an outbound-only Matrix Client-Server API client alongside one — all
            three format the same shared <code class="font-mono text-sm">summarizeSessionNotifyEvent()</code>
            text in their own house style (GitHub markdown with a 🔴/⚪/🟢 status
            dot, Slack mrkdwn emoji codes, Matrix plain text), so the wording
            stays consistent across channels.
          </p>
          <pre class="bg-[var(--color-bg)] border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-4 text-xs leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto"><code>&#123;
